1
00:00:17,093 --> 00:00:19,837
Hi, and I think we should say "goodbye"
哈囉 不過我想我們應該說再見了，

2
00:00:19,937 --> 00:00:21,700
because the filming is over.
畢竟影片都結束了

3
00:00:22,011 --> 00:00:23,122
Why?
為什麼？

4
00:00:25,564 --> 00:00:28,420
We've just talked to our father.
我們剛剛和我們的父親談過。

5
00:00:28,520 --> 00:00:33,374
He doesn't want to participate in this film anymore.
他不想再參與這部影片。

6
00:00:35,005 --> 00:00:37,913
It was fine with him as long as he could tell you
他會很配合--如果你讓完全

7
00:00:38,013 --> 00:00:40,396
exactly what to do and what to show.
他掌控拍什麼 說什麼等等一切。

8
00:00:41,056 --> 00:00:44,312
He wanted to glorify himself in front of the camera
他想要在鏡頭前榮耀他自己，

9
00:00:44,412 --> 00:00:47,048
but the truth is we quarrel all the time
但事實是我們永遠都在吵架

10
00:00:48,226 --> 00:00:50,775
and we can hardly make ends meet.
而且這爭吵似乎不會停止。

11
00:00:56,606 --> 00:00:58,539
So, what are you going to do with
那，你眼睛的檢驗

12
00:00:58,639 --> 00:01:00,668
the medical examination of your eyes?
該怎麼辦呢？

13
00:01:00,933 --> 00:01:04,962
I have no idea.
我也不知道。

14
00:01:05,974 --> 00:01:08,946
I would have to tell him that you want
我會告訴他，

15
00:01:09,046 --> 00:01:11,057
to help me with it.
你想要幫我去做這件事。

16
00:01:13,784 --> 00:01:14,202
And, you'll tell him that.
而你會負責告訴他。

17
00:01:16,175 --> 00:01:18,048
Out of reach
（有摸不到邊 之意）

18
00:01:20,589 --> 00:01:23,257
I'm with Karolina now. 
我現在Karolina一起，

19
00:01:23,357 --> 00:01:28,010
We've been watching some photos on the computer.
我們最近常在電腦上研究這些照片。

20
00:01:29,474 --> 00:01:30,012
And?
所以？

21
00:01:31,106 --> 00:01:32,663
Something's wrong with my eyes.
我的眼睛好像出了問題

22
00:01:32,763 --> 00:01:34,612
When I sit in front of the computer,
每當我坐在電腦前面時，

23
00:01:34,712 --> 00:01:35,928
I get a terrible headache.
我就頭痛欲裂

24
00:01:36,306 --> 00:01:37,261
And?
所以？

25
00:01:37,362 --> 00:01:41,516
Karolina smsed Kuba yesterday
Karolina 昨天傳簡訊給 Kuba

26
00:01:41,616 --> 00:01:45,084
and asked him if he could help us
問他能不能幫我們

27
00:01:46,126 --> 00:01:50,950
with arranging the medical examination of my eyes
安排一些眼睛的檢驗等等。

28
00:01:51,069 --> 00:01:51,612
And?
所以呢？

29
00:01:52,285 --> 00:01:56,078
And, he agreed but it has to be our decision.
他同意了，但是這必須你也要同意。

30
00:01:58,185 --> 00:02:00,393
But why are you arranging things behind my back?
但你為什麼瞞著我做這些安排？

31
00:02:01,001 --> 00:02:02,128
Karolina wrote to him, not me.
是Karolin寫信給他，不是我！

32
00:02:03,596 --> 00:02:05,070
You are really messing up things.
你真的很會搞砸事情

33
00:02:06,093 --> 00:02:07,284
What do you mean?
你是什麼意思？

34
00:02:08,967 --> 00:02:11,026
O.K. He can help you with the medical examination,
可-以-阿- 他可以幫你安排眼睛檢驗，

35
00:02:11,126 --> 00:02:13,001
but I don't want to have anything to do with him.
但我不想跟他扯其他上任何關係

36
00:02:13,878 --> 00:02:17,448
I don't want to do anything against you.
但我不想做違抗你的事情

37
00:02:17,548 --> 00:02:19,942
That's why I'm asking you.
這就是為什麼我會問你。

38
00:02:20,999 --> 00:02:23,868
Karolina wrote to him and he agreed to help,
Karolina傳簡訊給他而且他同意幫忙，

39
00:02:23,968 --> 00:02:26,253
but I want to have your permission first.
但我想要先有你的許可阿

40
00:02:28,838 --> 00:02:31,593
O.K. So, go and do it, but I don't want to see him anymore.
可-----以, 去做吧，但我不想要再看到他了

41
00:02:31,693 --> 00:02:33,069
There will be no more filming!
我不要再被拍了

42
00:02:34,609 --> 00:02:38,488
So, you've decided to come here with your sister, right?
所以...你和你姊妹一起來這邊是嘛？

43
00:02:40,604 --> 00:02:40,974
Yes. 是的

44
00:02:41,551 --> 00:02:48,643
You're 16. Why did't you come with your parents?
你才 16 歲。為什麼沒和你的父母來?

45
00:02:52,042 --> 00:02:54,525
Hold this book, all right?
拿著這本書好嗎

46
00:02:54,625 --> 00:02:58,891
Now, look at it and tell me what you can see.
現在，看著它，告訴我你能看到什麼？

47
00:02:59,392 --> 00:03:02,973
There are smaller signs here
這裡有些小標誌，

48
00:03:03,073 --> 00:03:06,754
and bigger signs over there.
還有一些大的在旁邊

49
00:03:08,371 --> 00:03:10,226
I can only see a different colour here.
我只能看到這邊有一塊不同的顏色

50
00:03:10,755 --> 00:03:13,003
All right.
好吧。

51
00:03:14,202 --> 00:03:16,380
I'm showing you my hand now.
現在我給你看我的手。

52
00:03:16,480 --> 00:03:18,737
How many fingers can you see?
你能看到多少根手指？

53
00:03:19,238 --> 00:03:20,013
I don't know.
我不知道。

54
00:03:21,738 --> 00:03:23,933
And now? Can you see my hand?
現在呢？你能看到我的手嗎？

55
00:03:32,404 --> 00:03:32,991
I can see it now.
我現在可以看到它。

56
00:03:34,318 --> 00:03:36,215
Can you count my fingers?
你能數我的手指嗎？

57
00:03:36,315 --> 00:03:40,005
How many fingers can you see with your left eye?
你用你的左眼能看到多少根手指？

58
00:03:40,392 --> 00:03:41,181
I can't tell.
我看不出來

59
00:03:42,350 --> 00:03:45,876
And now? Can you see anything?
而現在呢？你看到什麼？

60
00:03:48,108 --> 00:03:48,745
No.
我看不到。

61
00:03:49,976 --> 00:03:54,558
Usually, it's possible for an eye to recover provided
通常呢，眼睛是有機會恢復的，

62
00:03:54,658 --> 00:03:58,410
the problem is taken care of by the parents
但需要父母非常細心的照顧

63
00:03:59,227 --> 00:04:01,964
because you are still a child, aren't you?
因為你仍是個孩子，不是嗎？

64
00:04:02,397 --> 00:04:06,266
The problem, however, was ignored.
然而，這問題卻被忽略了

65
00:04:06,366 --> 00:04:11,849
The eye wasn't attended to with sufficient care.
這一隻眼睛沒有被好好的照顧

66
00:04:12,051 --> 00:04:17,962
and now it doesn't function at all.
而現在它已經不具備該有的功能了

67
00:04:19,394 --> 00:04:23,438
You're now 16 and for the last 16 years
你現在 16 歲，過去 16 年來

68
00:04:23,538 --> 00:04:26,924
your eyesight has been deteriorating.
你的視力一直在惡化。

69
00:04:27,300 --> 00:04:32,930
This means that it won't be possible for you to see
這意味著你另一隻眼睛很可能

70
00:04:33,030 --> 00:04:35,997
with your left eye at all.
也會逐漸失去功能

71
00:04:37,970 --> 00:04:39,919
Stop crying.
別哭了。

72
00:04:58,460 --> 00:05:00,759
I have no plans for the future.
我對未來有沒有計劃。

73
00:05:00,859 --> 00:05:01,954
Life is life.
生活就是生活。

74
00:05:02,382 --> 00:05:06,496
You're in a shitty situation because you're only 16.
你面臨一個滿慘的局面，因為你才 16 歲。

75
00:05:06,751 --> 00:05:09,745
I am sure I'll leave home sooner than you.
我相信我比你更早就會離開家。

76
00:05:09,746 --> 00:05:11,025
Do you want to bet?
你想要打賭嗎？

77
00:05:11,930 --> 00:05:13,864
Sure. A hundred zloty.
當然。一百個茲羅提。

78
00:05:25,358 --> 00:05:29,918
There was one card. Actually, it was not a card
本來有一張卡片，其實不是一張卡，

79
00:05:30,018 --> 00:05:32,968
but a big cup made of cardstock
是用一堆卡紙做的杯子

80
00:05:33,347 --> 00:05:39,029
that we prepared for the Father's Day.
是我們為了父親節準備的。

81
00:05:43,938 --> 00:05:46,123
We gave it to him with a note
我們在卡片上寫上 

82
00:05:46,223 --> 00:05:48,997
"for the best father in the world".
"給全世界最好的爸爸"

83
00:05:50,223 --> 00:05:52,344
It was the only thing that
這是我們唯一一次真的

84
00:05:52,444 --> 00:05:54,927
we really wanted to prepare for him.
很想為他做的

85
00:05:56,992 --> 00:05:59,967
And, we did it out of our own will.
而且，我們那樣做是出於我們自己的意願。

86
00:06:00,912 --> 00:06:02,803
That's your handwriting:
這就是你的字： 

87
00:06:02,903 --> 00:06:06,928
"Dad, on this joyous day I wish you good health,
爸爸，在這歡樂的一天我祝你身體健康，

88
00:06:07,028 --> 00:06:09,950
best of luck and may God bless you.
祝福你好運，並願上帝保佑你。

89
00:06:12,639 --> 00:06:16,908
I want you to be happy for the next thousand years
要再幸福一千年，

90
00:06:17,008 --> 00:06:20,929
and I hope you'll spend this time with Mum".
我希望你會和媽媽一起度過這時光。

91
00:06:23,999 --> 00:06:26,397
Sentence on behalf of the Republic of Poland
代表波蘭共和國反對

92
00:06:26,497 --> 00:06:28,710
against Bożena Siankowska.
Bożena Siankowska 的句子。

93
00:06:29,225 --> 00:06:31,807
And, we've got the reference number.
還有，我們找到社會號碼了。

94
00:06:33,039 --> 00:06:33,896
Another reference number.
另一組社會號碼。

95
00:06:34,295 --> 00:06:36,630
This is what we're looking for.
這是我們要找的。

96
00:06:36,634 --> 00:06:37,952
So, we need to borrow it from Dad.
所以，我們需要向爸爸借這個。

97
00:06:38,883 --> 00:06:40,968
It's enough if we copy it.
影印就好了啦

98
00:06:43,082 --> 00:06:46,429
We can find her ID number at the Citizens Advice Bureau
我們可以在公民諮詢局找到她的 ID 號碼，

99
00:06:46,529 --> 00:06:47,909
or take it from Grandma.
或從奶奶那邊找。

100
00:06:51,231 --> 00:06:54,017
Why would they give us our mother's ID number
公民諮詢局為什麼會願意給

101
00:06:54,117 --> 00:06:55,973
at the Citizens Advice Bureau?
我們她的ID號碼？

102
00:06:56,875 --> 00:06:57,963
We'll just tell them
我們就告訴他們

103
00:06:58,063 --> 00:06:59,911
that we're looking for our mother.
我們正在找我們的母親。

104
00:07:05,766 --> 00:07:06,034
Come in.
請進。

105
00:07:08,834 --> 00:07:09,953
Good morning.
早安。

106
00:07:11,022 --> 00:07:14,291
We've got little information about our mother because
我們只有一點點我們的母親的資訊，

107
00:07:14,391 --> 00:07:18,526
Klaudia was 2.5 and I was 3.5 years old when she left us
因為她是在 Klaudia 兩歲半，我3歲半的時候離開我們的。

108
00:07:19,102 --> 00:07:21,964
and we still don't know where she is.
而我們仍然不知道她在哪裡。

109
00:07:22,531 --> 00:07:28,722
Klaudia met our cousins who said she'd been put to jail.
Klaudia 遇見過一個親戚說 她去坐牢了。

110
00:07:29,222 --> 00:07:30,997
We don't know if she's in Poland or abroad.
我們不知道她是否還在波蘭或在國外。

111
00:07:31,351 --> 00:07:34,764
We also heard gossips that she'd been deported to Poland
我們還聽到謠言說，她曾被驅逐出波蘭，

112
00:07:34,864 --> 00:07:36,967
and was in prison somewhere here.
而且曾經在這裡的某個監獄。

113
00:07:38,505 --> 00:07:41,792
We have no access to any documents.
我們找不到任何相關文件。

114
00:07:42,008 --> 00:07:45,482
Does she use your father's surname or her maiden name?
她不會用你父親的姓或她的娘家的姓嗎？

115
00:07:45,857 --> 00:07:48,982
No idea. After the wedding, she used our father's name.
我們不知道。婚後她用了我們父親的名字。

116
00:07:49,994 --> 00:07:50,890
Actually, they didn't divorce.
實際上，他們沒有正式離婚。

117
00:07:50,990 --> 00:07:51,978
It was "annulment of marriage".
他們 ' 宣佈婚姻無效 '。

118
00:07:52,995 --> 00:07:54,987
She could have used her maiden name.
所以她可以用她的娘家姓。

119
00:07:56,015 --> 00:07:57,251
We don't know that.
我們不知道。

120
00:07:57,351 --> 00:07:59,257
She was pursued by police
她在法院還在審理離婚案的時候

121
00:07:59,357 --> 00:08:01,982
when the divorce case was still in court.
就被警察追補到案去了。

122
00:08:02,380 --> 00:08:03,672
She didn't come to court
她沒有出席

123
00:08:03,772 --> 00:08:05,805
for the marriage annulment verdict.
席法院的婚姻終止判決

124
00:08:06,235 --> 00:08:09,455
We just want to know if she's alive,
我們只是想知道是否她還活著，

125
00:08:09,555 --> 00:08:12,971
what's going on with her and where she is
她怎麼樣了 還有她在哪裡

126
00:08:13,779 --> 00:08:17,771
According to the penal code, as the injured party
根據刑法，作為受害方，

127
00:08:17,871 --> 00:08:20,988
you have access to the court files.
你有機會獲得法院的文件。

128
00:08:21,662 --> 00:08:24,350
I suggest you should go to court
我建議你應該

129
00:08:24,450 --> 00:08:26,994
and browse through the files
去法院查查看文件

130
00:08:28,145 --> 00:08:31,932
to find all the possible information about your mother.
去找關於你母親的所有可能資訊。

131
00:08:32,094 --> 00:08:36,047
This may help you get in touch with her.
這可能有助於你和她取得聯繫。

132
00:08:41,845 --> 00:08:44,718
Welcome to our sanctuary.
歡迎來到我們的聖所。

133
00:08:44,818 --> 00:08:46,879
Our alcohol den.
我們充滿酒精的巢穴。

134
00:08:57,980 --> 00:09:00,816
So, we've arrived at the place where we drink,
所以，我們現在在我們喝酒的地方，

135
00:09:00,916 --> 00:09:01,983
have parties…
開趴的地方......

136
00:09:03,089 --> 00:09:04,246
Where it smells.
有臭味的地方

137
00:09:04,431 --> 00:09:08,892
Where we sleep, play cards, play chess…
我們在這邊睡覺，打牌、 下棋......

138
00:09:09,636 --> 00:09:10,468
This is not me.
這不是我。

139
00:09:10,522 --> 00:09:11,300
This is you.
這是你。

140
00:09:11,914 --> 00:09:12,481
This is not me.
這不是我。

141
00:09:12,487 --> 00:09:12,977
This is you.
這是你。

142
00:09:13,842 --> 00:09:15,841
Klaudia，I remember having
我記得Klaudia以前有一套

143
00:09:15,941 --> 00:09:18,453
a completely different outfit at that time.
很美很美的衣服

144
00:09:19,929 --> 00:09:20,998
It was so pretty.
太漂亮了

145
00:09:21,212 --> 00:09:23,956
Oh, yes. A real beauty. Wait a second!
哦，對。超美的。等一下 ！

146
00:09:25,316 --> 00:09:26,540
Give me some of them.
給我一些。

147
00:09:26,640 --> 00:09:28,698
You're going through them so slowly.
你是看的好慢唷

148
00:09:32,076 --> 00:09:33,881
We don't have many memories of our Mum.
我們對媽媽其實沒有太多回憶，

149
00:09:33,981 --> 00:09:35,961
I don't remember what she actually looked like.
我甚至不記得她長什麼樣

150
00:09:36,129 --> 00:09:39,297
There was only one time when she came to visit us.
只有一次在她有來看我們，

151
00:09:39,397 --> 00:09:41,579
There are only three photos here.
在這裡只有三張照片。

152
00:09:42,487 --> 00:09:44,854
She showed up once to give us the bicycles
她那次給出現是為了給我們自行車，

153
00:09:44,954 --> 00:09:46,988
and she was wearing this white dress.
而且她穿著這件白色的洋裝。

154
00:09:48,953 --> 00:09:51,656
Yes, a "superman costume".
沒錯，是超人裝。

155
00:09:52,224 --> 00:09:56,972
It was a white, semi-transparent cloth and she had long blond hair.
它是一塊白色的半透明布，而且她有著長長的金髮。

156
00:09:57,335 --> 00:10:01,010
She was wearing sunglasses to hide her black eyes.
她戴著太陽鏡以隱藏她烏青的雙眼。

157
00:10:01,110 --> 00:10:04,728
Do you remember this gold bracelet she was wearing?
你還記得她帶著這個金手鐲嗎？

158
00:10:05,444 --> 00:10:06,525
Yes, rings and earrings.
對，還有戒指和耳環。

159
00:10:07,364 --> 00:10:11,070
Then, it turned out that she robbed a jeweller.
然後，原來她搶了一個珠寶商。

160
00:10:13,827 --> 00:10:16,755
If I was to see Bożena again, I would…
如果我能再見到我媽 Bożena ...

161
00:10:17,005 --> 00:10:19,155
She would tell you the same thing:
她會說同樣的話：

162
00:10:19,255 --> 00:10:21,247
"Sweetie, I had no choice".
親愛的，我別無選擇。

163
00:10:21,441 --> 00:10:22,726
I would kick her ass.
我會踢她的屁股。

164
00:10:22,826 --> 00:10:25,021
I wouldn't listen to her chattering.
我不會聽她的嘮叨。

165
00:10:25,391 --> 00:10:27,666
I would pay her back for all the 16 years
我會把她這十六年來

166
00:10:27,766 --> 00:10:29,995
when she wasn’t here on Mother's Day…
母親節的缺席一次奉還給她

167
00:10:30,212 --> 00:10:33,266
Nobody would be able to calm me down.
而且沒人能讓我平靜下來。

168
00:10:33,581 --> 00:10:36,164
Maybe violence is not the best way out,
暴力也許不是最好的出路，

